name: Swan couple
description: Once courtship is complete, male and female swans really are bonded for life, with few exceptions. This is unusual. Most other birds will raise their young as a pair for one season, but move on to new mates the next. What's more, many species also engage in "extra-pair mating" â€“ "adultery" to you and me. Ducks are particularly keen on such additional copulations. By finding extra mates in these ways, each bird can produce more offspring.
